{{See|Plus}}

==English==

===Conjunction===
'''plus'''

#(''arithmetic'') [[Increase]]d by.
#:''One '''plus''' one is two.''

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Dutch: plus, [[en]]
*Finnish: plus, [[ynnä]] (''archaic'')
*Italian: [[più]]
{{mid}}
{{bottom}}

===Noun===
'''plus''' (''plural:'' '''pluses''' or '''plusses''')

#An [[asset]] or [[useful]] [[addition]].
#:''He is a real '''plus''' to the team.''

====Synonyms====
*(''useful addition''): [[asset]]

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Dutch: [[meerwaarde]] {{f}}, {{m}}
*Finnish: [[etu]], [[plussa]]
{{mid}}
{{bottom}}

===Adjective===
'''plus'''

#Of a number, [[positive]] rather than a [[negative]] or [[zero]].
#:''-2 * -2 = +4'' ("minus 2 times minus 2 equals '''plus''' four")
#Positive, or involving [[advantage]].
#:''He is a '''plus''' factor.''

====Synonyms====
*(''of a number''): [[positive]]
*(''positive, involving advantage''): [[advantageous]], [[good]], [[positive]]

====Antonyms====
*(''of a number''): [[minus]], [[negative]]
*(''positive, involving advantage''): [[bad]], [[disadvantageous]], [[minus]], [[negative]]

====Translations====

'''number'''
